{% comment %}
  sections/path-chooser.liquid
  ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  The full-screen entry experience for Galactic Forge.

  Sequence:
    1. Black screen + "A long time ago, in a galaxy far, far away...."
    2. Intro fades out → split screen fades in
    3. Jedi crest + Sith emblem appear → titles → subtitles → buttons
    4. Hover: panel expands 60/40, lightsaber ignites on outer edge
    5. Click: choice saved to localStorage, entry screen fades out

  The chosen side ('light' | 'dark') is stored in localStorage under 'gf-side'
  and set as data-gf-side on <body> so the homepage can apply the right theme.
  ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
{% endcomment %}

{% comment %} Load section stylesheet — deduped by Shopify if called multiple times {% endcomment %}
{{ 'path-chooser.css' | asset_url | stylesheet_tag }}

<section id="gf-entry-screen" aria-label="Choose your path">

  {% comment %}
    ── Stars ──
    Decorative starfield sitting behind all other layers.
    Purely visual — aria-hidden keeps it invisible to screen readers.
  {% endcomment %}
  <div class="gf-stars" aria-hidden="true"></div>

  {% comment %}
    ── Intro Overlay ──
    Full-screen black panel shown before the split screen appears.
    aria-hidden: this is purely decorative atmosphere, not meaningful content.
  {% endcomment %}
  <div class="gf-intro" id="gfIntro" aria-hidden="true">
    <p class="gf-intro__text">A long time ago, in a galaxy far, far away....</p>
  </div>

  {% comment %}
    ── Crawl ──
    Hidden on load. JS shows this after the intro fades out.
    The perspective tilt and scroll animation are handled entirely in CSS.
    aria-hidden: decorative atmosphere, not meaningful content.
  {% endcomment %}
  <div class="gf-crawl" id="gfCrawl" aria-hidden="true">
    <div class="gf-crawl__inner">
      <div class="gf-crawl__text">

        <h2 class="gf-crawl__title">Galactic Forge</h2>

        <p>The galaxy's finest weapons and relics<br>have been gathered in one place.</p>

        <p>Artifacts forged in both light and darkness.<br>Ancient. Powerful. Legendary.</p>

        <p>But only those who choose their path<br>may enter the forge.</p>

        <p class="gf-crawl__closing">A PATH MUST BE CHOSEN.</p>

      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  {% comment %}
    ── Skip Button ──
    Always visible during the intro and crawl sequences.
    JS hides it once the split screen appears.
  {% endcomment %}
  <button class="gf-skip" id="gfSkip" type="button">Skip Intro</button>

  {% comment %}
    ── Split Screen ──
    Two panels, hidden on load. JS adds `.is-visible` after the intro finishes,
    which triggers the staggered CSS animations on the content inside.
  {% endcomment %}
  <div class="gf-split" id="gfSplit">

    {% comment %}
      ── Light Side Panel (left) ──
      role="button" + tabindex="0" makes the whole panel keyboard-focusable.
      The <button> inside has tabindex="-1" because the panel div handles focus.
    {% endcomment %}
    <div
      class="gf-panel gf-panel--light"
      data-side="light"
      role="button"
      tabindex="0"
      aria-label="Enter the Light Side"
    >
      <div class="gf-panel__inner">

        {% comment %} Jedi Order crest — SVG uses currentColor, controlled by CSS {% endcomment %}
        <div class="gf-emblem">
          {% render 'icon-jedi-crest' %}
        </div>

        <h2 class="gf-panel__title">Light Side</h2>
        <p class="gf-panel__subtitle">Choose your path</p>

        <button class="gf-btn gf-btn--light" type="button" tabindex="-1" aria-hidden="true">
          Enter
        </button>

      </div>
    </div>

    {% comment %}
      ── Dark Side Panel (right) ──
    {% endcomment %}
    <div
      class="gf-panel gf-panel--dark"
      data-side="dark"
      role="button"
      tabindex="0"
      aria-label="Enter the Dark Side"
    >
      <div class="gf-panel__inner">

        {% comment %} Sith Order emblem — SVG uses currentColor, controlled by CSS {% endcomment %}
        <div class="gf-emblem">
          {% render 'icon-sith-emblem' %}
        </div>

        <h2 class="gf-panel__title">Dark Side</h2>
        <p class="gf-panel__subtitle">Embrace your destiny</p>

        <button class="gf-btn gf-btn--dark" type="button" tabindex="-1" aria-hidden="true">
          Enter
        </button>

      </div>
    </div>

  </div>

</section>

{% comment %} Load script deferred — runs after the DOM is ready {% endcomment %}
<script src="{{ 'path-chooser.js' | asset_url }}" defer></script>
